<div class='function'><span class='function_name'><a class='anchor' id='text_input.__init__'>text_input</a>.<b>__init__(form, text=u'', frame=True, center=False, stub=u'Type here ...', return_accepts=False, var=None)</b></span><div class='details'>
Constructor.<br />
<br />
<span class='keyword'>Arguments:</span>
<br />
<span class='variable'>form </span> &rarr;  The parent form.
<br />
<br />
<span class='keyword'>Keyword arguments:</span>
<br />
<span class='variable'>text </span> &rarr;  The text to start with (default=u'').
<br />
<span class='variable'>frame </span> &rarr;  Indicates whether a frame should be drawn around the widget
<br />
(default=False).<br />
<span class='variable'>center </span> &rarr;  Indicates whether the text should be centered (default=False).
<br />
<span class='variable'>stub </span> &rarr;  A text string that should be shown whenever the user has not
<br />
entered any text (default=u'Type here ...').<br />
<span class='variable'>return_accepts </span> &rarr;  Indicates whether a return press should accept and
<br />
close the form (default=False).<br />
<span class='variable'>var </span> &rarr;  The name of the experimental variable that should be used to log
<br />
the widget status (default=None).<br />
</div></div>
